        "inputs": {
          "note": "CC. Configuring for OpeRouter API:\n\n1. Create a new chatflow or open an existing one. \n2. Drag and drop an OpenAI Chat Model node onto the canvas.\n3. Connect the OpenAI Chat Model node to your flow.  In the node's configuration panel, create the credential usimg the API base URL and the specific model name:\n\n4.  Find the Additional Parameters (sometimes called \"Base Path\" or \"Base Options\") section within the OpenAI Chat Model node's configuration.\n\n5.  Set the Base URL (or Base Path) to https://openrouter.ai/api/v1.\n\n6.   In the Model Name field, enter the specific OpenRouter model identifier you wish to use (e.g., anthropic/claude-3-5-sonnet or openai/gpt-4o). "
        },
